rComments: Worst experience as a student ever! To think I actually used to be a fan of him and his work.

He didn't even bother handing out a course syllabus on the 1st day. Instead he went about trying to get people to drop his course so he would have fewer students, changed the scheduled course time and complained about those who didn't take his )apparently boring and easy) prerequisite survey course. A dud.

Should retire from teaching and just stick to being a curator-that is his true talent, not professorhsip. Course is hard because he is not clear on his expectations. Not very supportive or helpful when you want him to clarify his requirements.
Alright as a professor (considering he is a curator professionally), but he whouls mark work instead of his TA's.
He's soooo BORING!!!  If I wanted to read your book, since I've been forced to buy it for your class...then I would read it myself, and not attend your lectures where you simply read the book to us!
